The paper deals with complexity theory and communication complexity, which are central topics in computer science. The use of quantum computing and the techniques of generalized discrepancy and polynomial method suggest that the paper may belong to the categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses XOR lemmas and threshold direct product theorems, which are related to topics in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science, indicating that it may also belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
